# Zippy — environment.
#
# The redirect Worker's runtime config does NOT live here — Cloudflare Workers read
# their config from wrangler.toml + secrets, not a root .env.local:
#
#   BASE_URL   → services/redirect/wrangler.toml  [vars]   (builds the shortUrl)
#   API_TOKEN  → `bunx wrangler secret put API_TOKEN`       (gates POST/GET /api/links)
#   LINKS (KV) → services/redirect/wrangler.toml  [[kv_namespaces]]
#
# For LOCAL `wrangler dev`, put dev secrets in services/redirect/.dev.vars (gitignored):
#   API_TOKEN="a-local-dev-token"
#
# ── Deploy (optional — for `wrangler deploy` from CI or your machine) ──
# The code doesn't read these; they live in your shell / CI environment.
# Cloudflare (dashboard → Account ID / API Tokens, token with Workers KV edit):
# CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=
# CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
